  "dice1text": {
    "id": "dice1text",
    "x": 50,
    "y": 400,
    "width": 300,
    "z": 185,
    "movable": false,
    "movableInEdit": false,
    "css": "font-size: 22px; ",
    "text": "The 3D 2-sided dice has 'shape3d' set to 'd2-flip'. It flips around the horizontal axis. The edge has some thickness and the color can be changed using the css '--edgeColor'. In the example above it is red."
  },
  "dice2text": {
    "id": "dice2text",
    "x": 400,
    "y": 400,
    "width": 300,
    "z": 185,
    "movable": false,
    "movableInEdit": false,
    "css": "font-size: 20px; ",
    "text": "The 3D 6-sided dice has rounded corners so it uses a custom animation to hide the other faces that would peek through at the corners from behind. This does leave a small artifact in the corners for a fraction of a second at the end of the roll. That is normal and not fixable."
  },
  "dice3text": {
    "id": "dice3text",
    "x": 750,
    "y": 400,
    "width": 300,
    "z": 185,
    "movable": false,
    "movableInEdit": false,
    "css": "font-size: 21px; ",
    "text": "The cube dice has 4 different images for each value to reflect all possible orientations in a real-world dice. The coloring is automatic, but you can overridde each face and the pips using the 'svgReplaces' values on the dice."
  },
  "dice4text": {
    "id": "dice4text",
    "x": 1100,
    "y": 400,
    "width": 300,
    "z": 185,
    "movable": false,
    "movableInEdit": false,
    "css": "font-size: 20px; ",
    "text": "If using images on dice, you can change the 'imageScale' property to find the best size that fits. The dice above uses 0.8 instead of the default 1. This only changes the scale of the image and not the whole dice. And it applies to all faces. If you want different imageScale on each face, see the Appearance variant."
  },
  "dice5text": {
    "id": "dice5text",
    "x": 50,
